      "subject_input": "We finished 12 interviews across 3 plants.  Common things we heard: operators say they waste time looking for tools, supervisors want real-time status boards, maintenance crew says preventive schedules are ignored, and everyone complains about the ERP being too slow. Help us synthesize this.\n",
      "subject_output": "\n\nGood data from multiple sources \u2014 now let's find the patterns underneath the surface complaints.\n\n**Don't take findings at face value.** Each statement is an observation. Synthesis asks *why* and *what connects them*.\n\n**Let's cluster what you've heard:**\n\n**Cluster 1: Information isn't where the work happens**\n- Operators waste time looking for tools \u2192 *Where is tool location tracked? Is it tracked at all?*\n- ERP is \"too slow\" \u2192 *Slow to load, or slow to answer the question they actually have?*\n- Supervisors want status boards \u2192 *What information are they currently missing, and when?*\n\nThese may share a root cause: **people can't get the right information at the point of need without leaving their workflow.**\n\n**Cluster 2: Planned processes break down in practice**\n- Preventive maintenance schedules ignored \u2192 *Why? Understaffed? Conflicting production pressure? Schedules don't match reality?*\n- This likely connects to tool availability \u2014 if tools are missing, maintenance gets deferred.\n\n**Cluster 3: Workaround culture**\n- If the ERP is too slow, what do people use instead? This is the question you should answer from your notes.\n\n**Before finalizing themes, check your data:**\n\n| Validation Question | Why It Matters |\n|---|---|\n| Did operators across all 3 plants describe tool-finding problems, or just one? | Single-plant issues \u2260 systemic themes |\n| When supervisors say \"real-time status,\" what specifically do they want to see? | \"Status board\" is another frozen request |\n| Who *decides* to skip preventive maintenance \u2014 operators, supervisors, or production pressure from above? | Root cause determines the right framing |\n| What does \"ERP is too slow\" mean literally? Seconds? Minutes? Or \"it doesn't answer my actual question\"? | Speed vs. relevance are different problems |\n\n**Now write insight statements for each cluster:**\n\nThe formula is: *observation \u2192 inference \u2192 insight*\n\nFor example:\n- **Observation:** Operators across 3 plants spend significant time locating tools\n- **Inference:** ...because tool location isn't tracked or visible at the workstation\n- **Insight:** ...which means the system design assumes workers have information that actually lives only in people's heads or informal systems\n\n**Your homework before brainstorming:**\n\n1. Go through your 12 interviews and count how many *independently* mentioned each theme \u2014 that's your confidence level\n2. Check for missing voices: did you talk to anyone who does preventive maintenance? Did you hear from night shift?\n3. Write 2-3 \"How Might We\" questions per validated theme\n\nFor example: *\"How might we give operators immediate access to tool and part locations without leaving their workstation?\"*\n\nWhich of these clusters resonates most with what you heard across all three plants?"
