      "subject_input": "Our synthesis produced three themes: tool accessibility on the floor, real-time communication gaps, and misaligned maintenance schedules. We want to brainstorm solutions.  There are 6 of us in the room.\n",
      "subject_output": "\n\nThree validated themes and six people \u2014 solid starting point. Here's how to structure your session.\n\n**Ground Rules (post these visibly)**\n\n1. **No evaluation during idea generation.** If someone says \"that won't work,\" redirect: *\"Save that for convergence.\"*\n2. Quantity over quality \u2014 aim for **20+ ideas** before grouping anything\n3. Rough one-liners only \u2014 no detailed proposals\n4. Build on each other's ideas \u2014 \"yes, and...\"\n5. Constraints are creative fuel, not blockers\n\n**Session Structure (~90 minutes)**\n\n**Round 1: Divergent Ideation (45 min)**\n\nRun three 15-minute sprints, one per theme. Each sprint follows the same pattern:\n\n| Minutes | Activity |\n|---|---|\n| 0-3 | State the theme and one key constraint from your research |\n| 3-10 | Silent writing \u2014 everyone writes ideas individually, one per sticky note |\n| 10-15 | Share and build \u2014 read aloud, riff off each other's ideas |\n\n**Constraint prompts to fuel each sprint:**\n\n*Tool Accessibility:*\n- \"Workers have greasy hands and can't easily use screens...\"\n- \"Tools move between stations and shifts...\"\n- \"What if the tool could tell you where it is?\"\n\n*Communication Gaps:*\n- \"Supervisors cover multiple lines and can't be everywhere...\"\n- \"Shift handoff loses context...\"\n- \"What if the information traveled with the work, not the person?\"\n\n*Maintenance Misalignment:*\n- \"Production pressure overrides scheduled maintenance...\"\n- \"The people who schedule aren't the people who execute...\"\n- \"What if maintenance timing adapted to actual production state?\"\n\n**Round 2: Perspective Multiplication (15 min)**\n\nTake your best 10 ideas and ask:\n- How does a **night-shift operator** experience this?\n- How does a **new hire in week one** experience this?\n- How does this work during an **equipment emergency**?\n\nThis stress-tests ideas and generates new ones.\n\n**Round 3: Convergence (30 min)**\n\n1. Spread all ideas out visibly\n2. **Cluster by underlying philosophy**, not surface features:\n   - \"Bring information to the worker\" vs \"bring the worker to information\"\n   - \"Prevent the problem\" vs \"speed up the response\"\n   - \"Individual tools\" vs \"team-wide visibility\"\n3. Name each cluster by its philosophy \u2014 aim for 3-5 themes\n4. Don't vote yet. Just group and name.\n\n**Facilitation tips for 6 people:**\n\n- Rotate who reads ideas aloud to prevent one voice dominating\n- If someone goes quiet, directly invite: *\"What are you thinking about this one?\"*\n- When energy stalls, introduce a constraint flip: *\"What if we had unlimited budget? Now what if we had zero budget?\"*\n- Park detailed discussions: *\"Great detail \u2014 write it on the parking lot and let's keep generating\"*\n\n**After the session, capture:**\n- Photos of all sticky note clusters\n- Philosophy name for each cluster\n- Which themes have ideas from multiple people (signals strength)\n- Any \"parking lot\" items for later\n\nWhat time of day are you running this? Energy levels matter for ideation quality."
