      "subject_input": "You suggested looking for recurring themes but I'm still stuck. I read through all the notes and I don't see any patterns. Everything feels unique to each person.  I really don't know what to look for.\n",
      "subject_output": "\n\nThat feeling of \"everything is unique\" usually means you're reading at the wrong altitude. You're seeing *details* \u2014 which are different per person \u2014 instead of *structures*, which repeat.\n\n**Try this reframing exercise.**\n\nFor each data point from your interviews, ask these three questions:\n\n**Question 1: What is this person trying to accomplish?**\n\nNot the specific task \u2014 the underlying goal.\n\n- Person A: *\"I walk to the warehouse to count parts myself\"*\n- Person B: *\"I call three people before I get an answer on stock levels\"*\n- Person C: *\"I keep my own spreadsheet of what we actually have\"*\n\nThese look like three unique behaviors. But the goal is identical: **getting inventory information they can trust.**\n\n**Question 2: What's stopping them?**\n\nAgain, ignore the specifics. Look at the *type* of barrier.\n\n- *\"The system is too slow\"* \u2192 barrier: **tool doesn't meet the speed of their work**\n- *\"Nobody updates the log\"* \u2192 barrier: **process depends on manual compliance**\n- *\"Night shift can't reach anyone\"* \u2192 barrier: **knowledge lives in people, not systems**\n\n**Question 3: What did they do instead?**\n\nWorkarounds are your richest pattern source, because people independently inventing similar workarounds is the strongest signal you'll find.\n\n| What they did | Workaround type |\n|---|---|\n| Built a personal spreadsheet | Created a shadow system |\n| Walked to physically check | Bypassed the system entirely |\n| Called a specific person who \"just knows\" | Relied on human knowledge base |\n| Wrote notes on a whiteboard | Made information visible and ambient |\n\n**Now \u2014 go through your notes one more time, but this time create three columns:**\n\n| Trying To... | Blocked By... | So They... |\n|---|---|---|\n| Confirm stock level | System data is stale | Walks to warehouse |\n| Get repair guidance | Manual is in break room | Calls senior operator |\n| Know equipment status | No real-time visibility | Checks machines in person |\n| Hand off shift context | No structured handoff tool | Relies on verbal summary |\n\n**Patterns will emerge in the columns, not in the individual rows.** When the \"Blocked By\" column shows the same barrier type across different people doing different tasks \u2014 that's your theme.\n\nTry this with just five of your data points right now. What are those five people each *trying to accomplish*?"
