      "subject_input": "We started prototyping (Method 6) but realized we missed a key stakeholder group \u2014 the night shift operators.  Their workflow is completely different.  I think we need to go back to research.\n",
      "subject_output": "\n\nThat's the design process working correctly \u2014 not a setback. Discovering this gap during lo-fi prototyping is exactly when you want to find it, not after building the full solution.\n\n**Yes, go back to Method 2, but keep it targeted.**\n\nYou don't need to redo all your research. You need a focused investigation to fill this specific gap.\n\n**Targeted Research Plan:**\n\n**What to investigate (3-5 sessions, not 12):**\n\n| Activity | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| Shadow 1-2 night shift operators for a full shift | See workflow differences firsthand |\n| Interview 2-3 night shift operators on the floor | Hear their specific pain points in context |\n| Observe a shift handoff from day to night | Understand what information transfers and what gets lost |\n\n**Questions designed for the gap:**\n\n- *\"Walk me through your shift from start to finish \u2014 what's different about working nights?\"*\n- *\"When you need help or information at 2 AM, what do you do?\"*\n- *\"We're building [brief concept description] \u2014 what would need to change for it to work on your shift?\"*\n- *\"What do you know about the problems that day shift doesn't?\"*\n\n**What you're specifically looking for:**\n\n| Dimension | Day Shift (known) | Night Shift (investigate) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Support access | Supervisors, peers, engineers nearby | Who's available? How far away? |\n| Information sources | System + ask colleagues | System + what else? |\n| Decision authority | Escalation path is clear | Who decides at 2 AM? |\n| Workarounds | Known from earlier research | Likely different \u2014 night shift invents their own |\n| Environmental differences | Standard conditions | Lighting, staffing density, noise profile may differ |\n\n**After the targeted research:**\n\n1. **Return to Method 3** \u2014 add night shift findings to your existing synthesis. Do your current themes hold, or do they need revision?\n2. **Update your concepts** \u2014 do your Method 5 concepts work for night shift, or do they need variants?\n3. **Resume Method 6** \u2014 prototype with night shift constraints included. Test prototypes *during* a night shift, not during the day.\n\n**The cost of this loop:** roughly one week of targeted research plus synthesis revision.\n\n**The cost of skipping it:** building a solution that 30-40% of your users can't or won't use, and discovering that after full deployment.\n\nHow soon can you get access to the night shift floor?"
