      "subject_input": "We're working on Method 3 synthesis.  I noticed that two interviewees mentioned a workaround where they text photos to their supervisor.  Is that significant?\n",
      "subject_output": "\n\nTwo people independently describing the same workaround is a meaningful signal. But the significance isn't the workaround itself \u2014 it's what the workaround reveals about unmet needs.\n\n**Unpack it with three questions:**\n\n**What need does the photo texting serve?**\n- Is it proof of a problem? (\"Look at this broken part\")\n- Is it a request for guidance? (\"What do I do about this?\")\n- Is it status communication? (\"Here's where we are\")\n- Is it covering themselves? (\"I documented that I reported this\")\n\nEach answer points to a different underlying theme.\n\n**Why a photo specifically?**\n- Text descriptions aren't sufficient \u2014 the problem is visual or spatial\n- The formal reporting system doesn't support images, or is too slow\n- A photo is faster than writing a description, especially under time pressure\n- Photos carry context that words don't \u2014 location, severity, surrounding conditions\n\n**Why texting instead of the official channel?**\n- The official system is too slow or cumbersome\n- Texting gets an immediate human response\n- The formal channel doesn't reach the right person\n- There's trust in the personal relationship that the system doesn't provide\n\n**Now check your other interviews:**\n\n| Look For | Why |\n|---|---|\n| Others who mention texting, calling, or messaging outside official systems | Same workaround pattern strengthens the theme |\n| Others who describe *different* workarounds for the same underlying need | Multiple workarounds for one need = strong signal |\n| Anyone who *doesn't* have a workaround for the same situation | Why not? Different shift, different access, different expectations? |\n\n**Where this might fit in your synthesis:**\n\nThis likely clusters with a theme around **\"formal communication channels don't match the speed, richness, or directness that the work demands.\"** Check whether other data points \u2014 slow ERP, verbal handoffs, whiteboard notes \u2014 share